REVIEW: Here's a tool we expose to our customer-support agent so it can look up whatever it needs from our Postgres:

{
  "name": "run_query",
  "description": "Run a SQL query against the app database and return rows.",
  "input_schema": {"type": "object", "properties": {"sql": {"type": "string"}}, "required": ["sql"]}
}

The model writes whatever SQL it needs. We tell it in the system prompt to only read, never write, and to stay on the current tenant. It's been working great in testing. Anything to worry about?
